    "default_locale": "en-US",
    "description": {
        "en-US": "This requires your OwnCloud server to have public link sharing enabled and optionally to have the OAuth2 plugin enabled for creating an app authentication token.\n\nNextCloud should work with the default settings\n\nThis extension requires 4 pieces of data: \n<ol><li>your WebDAV URL, which you can get from your personal Settings after you log in to your cloud service</li><li>your username</li><li>your password OR an app token you generate</li><li>the path where you want your attachments saved to.</li></ol>\nThere is a known issue with Thunderbird itself where if you save an email draft and then re-open it, you will be unable to delete the attachment."
    },
